case.name: Blessing!
case.description: Aqua will use the luck buffing spell "Blessing" on herself after losing a few times. This is by most accounts, cheating, or at least seen as a dirty tactic.

notes.note: I believe Aqua is actually too lazy to go through with this, so that could potentially come up if Noire mentions the work it takes to be an idol.

As it would turn out, lazing around and eating snacks is something Aqua herself is very guilty of. Aqua can't lie, but she will try to avoid putting herself in a position where she has to admit that she ALSO does what Noire is accusing Neptune of doing. So that's why she's reacting the way she is in this line.
Yes this is an exceedingly dumb question
Aqua DOES know about the "real world" so it wouldn't be unreasonable to believe she knows about Uno, however I think it's funny if she doesn't know/forgot
I'm thinking I might have Aqua insist that he joins her party depending on how he answers. But you can have him answer however you wish! (^-^)b

It's worth noting that her water and holy magic are most definitely NOT enough to handle everything. Best exemplified with her crippling inability to do anything to giant toads, whom resist water attacks and are not evil, so holy magic doesn't do much of anything. This could be a topic of conversation for one of Aqua's strips if you'd like.

This could easily lead to other targets related to what Nami has seen in the great blue sea, which I assume is quite a lot. So for this line of dialogue it's perfectly fine if you pick something shorter since Nami only has two lines left for this strip. Other more complex sights or places she's visited could be explored in later strips.
Just fyi, these lines have different markers
